    public static enum GameState.EntityType
extends java.lang.Enum<GameState.EntityType>
    The EntityType enum represents a set of possible types an entity in the environment may be. Ranging from Empty to Player to HealthPack, and much more.
    Author:
    ERAU AI Club

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants

      Empty

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Empty

        public static final GameState.EntityType Empty
        There is no entity.

      • Wall

        public static final GameState.EntityType Wall
        The entity is a wall, impassable by projectiles, players, and mines.

      • Player

        public static final GameState.EntityType Player
        The entity is a AI-controlled player that interacts with the environment by moving, shooting, and placing mines.

      • Mine

        public static final GameState.EntityType Mine
        The entity is a mine. Explodes and hurt any Player that comes in contact with it by 1 health point. Also, explodes when in contact with any Projectile or Storm, destroying both in the process.

      • Projectile

        public static final GameState.EntityType Projectile
        The entity is a projectile. Hurts hostile Player by 1 health point. Also, projectiles can be destroyed when in contact with any other Mine or Projectile.

      • HealthPack

        public static final GameState.EntityType HealthPack
        The entity is a health pack. Any Player that comes in contact with it gains 1 health point. Also, health packs can be destroyed when in contact with any other Mine or Projectile.

      • Storm

        public static final GameState.EntityType Storm
        The entity is a storm. Instantly kills any Player when in contact. Also, destroys everything it touches, including: Wall, Mine, Projectile, and HealthPack.
